    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1038_s41592_023_02139_9__task_001/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The key innovation of our algorithm is the use of a matrix-free spectral embedding algorithm to project single-cell omics data into a low-dimensional space that preserves the intrinsic geometric properties of the underlying data... This strategy substantially shortens the time and space complexity, making it linearly proportional to the number of cells in the single-cell data.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly claims linear time and space complexity for the matrix-free spectral embedding algorithm. However, the paper's largest benchmark dataset tested was 200,000 cells (not 10M+), so the claim about 10M+ cells is extrapolated from the paper's stated algorithmic properties rather than empirically demonstrated.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-023-02139-9",
