      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SnapATAC2 stood out by requiring only 21 GB of memory to process 200,000 cells (Fig. 1d). In contrast, the original SnapATAC package showed limitations, encountering out-of-memory errors when handling over 80,000 cells on a server with 500 GB of available memory.",
