    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/compressed-sparse-row-matrix-handling/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To address this barrier, we devised a matrix-free spectral embedding algorithm that efficiently computes eigenvectors using the Lanczos algorithm, eliminating the need for constructing a full similarity matrix... This method exhibits linear space and time usage relative to the input matrix size, resulting in a faster and memory-efficient approach for processing of large datasets.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes matrix-free spectral embedding and its memory efficiency, but does NOT explicitly mention CSR (compressed sparse row) format by name. Paper uses sparse matrices implicitly (e.g., 'sparse matrix representing all cells' contact maps' in passage 13) but does not detail CSR conversion as a task. The algorithm works with sparse data but CSR format is not explicitly discussed as a conversion step.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-023-02139-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "compressed-sparse-row-matrix-handling",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Convert and initialize single-cell count matrices into compressed sparse row (CSR) format compatible with matrix-free spectral embedding and scalable dimension reduction algorithms.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:44:33.488869+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/compressed-sparse-row-matrix-handling/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For example, the memory usage of the similarity matrix for a dataset with one million cells is approximately 7 TB, far beyond the capacity of most computational servers... our algorithm achieves the same goal while avoiding this computationally expensive step... making it linearly proportional to the number of cells in the single-cell data.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper demonstrates memory efficiency for large datasets (up to 200,000 cells tested, with discussion of 1M cells) and linear scaling, but does not explicitly name CSR format or discuss it as the solution. The paper's matrix-free approach avoids constructing full matrices, but CSR is not named as the underlying format.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-023-02139-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "compressed-sparse-row-matrix-handling",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "CSR representation is essential for memory-efficient processing of large sparse single-cell datasets (10M+ cells)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:44:33.488869+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/compressed-sparse-row-matrix-handling/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For example, the memory usage of the similarity matrix for a dataset with one million cells is approximately 7 TB, far beyond the capacity of most computational servers.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper discusses memory constraints at 1M cells but does not explicitly recommend CSR format as the solution. The matrix-free algorithm is presented as the solution, not CSR conversion.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-023-02139-9",
