    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/computational-complexity-validation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To benchmark the performance of SnapATAC2, we generated synthetic scATAC-seq datasets with varying cell numbers and compared the scalability of the matrix-free spectral embedding algorithm to other widely used dimensionality reduction algorithms... Our findings, illustrated in Fig. 1c, show that SnapATAC2, along with ArchR, Signac and EpiScanpy, had the least increase in runtime as the number of cells in the dataset expanded... Regarding memory efficiency, SnapATAC2 stood out by requiring only 21 GB of memory to process 200,000 cells (Fig. 1d).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper validates complexity claims but only up to 200,000 cells, not 10M+ cells as claimed in the research question. The paper does measure runtime and memory against cell count and plots results, confirming linear scaling behavior, but the scale is substantially smaller than the 10M+ cells specified in the card.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-023-02139-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "computational-complexity-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Empirically validate theoretical time and space complexity claims of a scalable algorithm by executing it on progressively large datasets (10M+ cells), measuring wall-clock runtime and peak memory, and plotting observed metrics against the predicted complexity curve to confirm li",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:44:54.089384+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/computational-complexity-validation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We have implemented these algorithmic advancements in a Python package called SnapATAC2... The key innovation of our algorithm is the use of a matrix-free spectral embedding algorithm to project single-cell omics data into a low-dimensional space... To express the cosine similarity using matrix operations, we first rescale the nonnegative count matrix C to obtain a new matrix X, such that the rows of X have unit L2 norm.",
      "asbval:note": "SnapATAC2 confirmed as the tool; matrix-free spectral embedding with cosine similarity confirmed. CSR format handling is implied by the sparse matrix operations described.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-023-02139-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "computational-complexity-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "SnapATAC2 - Algorithm under test; provides tl.spectral (matrix-free spectral embedding with cosine similarity metric) and dataset utilities for loading/generating large count matrices in CSR format.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:44:54.089384+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
