    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/cosine-similarity-metric-application/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "In this section, we introduce a matrix-free algorithm for spectral embedding that avoids calculating the similarity matrix. This approach is specifically designed for cosine similarity... To express the cosine similarity using matrix operations, we first rescale the nonnegative count matrix C to obtain a new matrix X, such that the rows of X have unit L2 norm. Consequently, the cosine similarity matrix between rows of X can be represented as XXT.",
      "asbval:note": "Cosine similarity is explicitly confirmed as the core metric for matrix-free spectral embedding. Applicability across modalities (scATAC-seq, scRNA-seq, scHi-C, methylation) is demonstrated in passages 6-7.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-023-02139-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "cosine-similarity-metric-application",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
