    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/cosine-similarity-metric-application/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We have implemented these algorithmic advancements in a Python package called SnapATAC2... The key innovation of our algorithm is the use of a matrix-free spectral embedding algorithm to project single-cell omics data into a low-dimensional space that preserves the intrinsic geometric properties of the underlying data.",
      "asbval:note": "SnapATAC2 is confirmed as the implementation vehicle. Cosine similarity is the default (passage 9 confirms it is 'specifically designed for cosine similarity').",
